==Old English==

===Etymology===
From the same West Germanic base as [[dæg|dæġ]].  Cognate with Middle Dutch ''daghen'' (Dutch [[dagen]]), Old High German [[tagen|tagēn]] (German [[tagen]]).

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/'daɣian/}}

===Verb===
'''dagian''' (class 2 weak)
# to [[dawn]]
#:''Ne ðis ne dagaþ eastan.''  This dawns not from the east. (''The Fight at Finnsburh'')

====Derived terms====
*[[dagung]]

===Descendants===
*English [[daw]]


